02/03/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- The government on Wednesday (2 March) is to begin discussing the extension of its customs union agreement with the EU, to include the ten countries that entered the Union last May. The issue is seen as a step towards Turkey's formal recognition of Cyprus and is a pre-condition for opening EU membership negotiations with Ankara. 
In other news, Justice Minister Cemil Cicek announced on Tuesday that the government has information about the whereabouts of the scandal-plagued Uzan family. Members of the family are wanted for mass fraud that totalled billions of dollars and damaged state interests. (TurkishPress.com, AFP, NTV - 01/03/05)
